  "appearance": {
    "en": "Coconut Oil is a white to light yellow mass or a colorless or light yellow, clear oil. It has a slight, characteris-tic odor and a mild taste. It is freely soluble in diethyl ether and in petroleum ether. It is practically insoluble in water. At a temperature below 159C, it congeals to a hard and brittle solid. Melting point: 20 – 289C Acid value <1.13> Not more than 0.2. Saponification value <1.13> 246 – 264 Unsaponifiable matter <1.13> Not more than 1.0z. Iodine value <1.13> 7 – 11"
  },
  "storageConditions": {
    "en": "Containers—Tight containers."
  }
}